The paper proposes a new algorithm for recovery of sparse vectors from underdetermined measurements, which is a common problem in the field of compressed sensing. The paper also discusses optimization schemes and convergence guarantees for the proposed algorithm. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves machine learning techniques and statistical analysis, which are covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.ST (Statistics). The paper also discusses signal processing techniques, which are covered in cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper involves numerical analysis and optimization, which are covered in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Systems and Control).
